@startuml
title Intent mandatory profile proposal

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #424242
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #424242

rectangle "TMF921 Intent\nbase resource model" as TMF #EEF2FF

rectangle "Intent management entity\nmandatory profile\n\nTMF-aligned, not TMF-minimal" as PROFILE #E8F5E9

TMF --> PROFILE : intent management entity conformance\ndefines minimum runtime Intent profile

rectangle "Minimal create request" as CREATE #FFF8E1 {
  rectangle "Mandatory machine-readable fields\n\n- name\n- expression\n- expression.@type\n- expression.iri\n- expression.expressionValue\n- @type\n- @baseType" as CREATE_MIN

  rectangle "Strongly recommended\nfor traceability and speed\n\n- humanExpression\n- intentSpecification.id" as CREATE_RECOMMENDED

  rectangle "Optional / governed enrichment\n\n- description\n- validFor\n- relatedParty\n- priority\n- externalId" as CREATE_OPTIONAL
}

rectangle "IntentSpecification resolution" as RESOLUTION #FFE0B2 {
  rectangle "If intentSpecification.id supplied\n\n- authoritative\n- must reference ACTIVE spec\n- must align with expression.iri" as SPEC_ID_SUPPLIED

  rectangle "If intentSpecification.id omitted\n\nResolve ACTIVE IntentSpecification\nusing expression.iri" as SPEC_ID_OMITTED

  rectangle "Reject request if\n\n- zero ACTIVE matches\n- multiple ACTIVE matches\n- supplied id conflicts with iri" as REJECT
}

rectangle "Persisted / admitted Intent" as PERSISTED #E0F2F1 {
  rectangle "Mandatory persisted response fields\n\n- id\n- href\n- name\n- version\n- lifecycleStatus\n- statusReason\n- statusChangeDate\n- intentSpecification.id\n- expression\n- expression.@type\n- expression.iri\n- expression.expressionValue\n- @type\n- @baseType" as PERSISTED_MIN

  rectangle "Resolved specification is recorded\n\nintentSpecification.id becomes\nmandatory after admission" as SPEC_RECORDED
}

rectangle "Lifecycle and version projection" as LIFECYCLE #E3F2FD {
  rectangle "Top-level lifecycleStatus\n= external lifecycle projection" as STATUS
  rectangle "version\n= projected runtime version" as VERSION
  rectangle "activeVersion\n= version driving projection\nwhere a pointer is exposed" as ACTIVE_VERSION
}

rectangle "Fuller implementation profile" as FULLER #F3E5F5 {
  rectangle "Useful enrichments\n\n- humanExpression\n- intentSpecification.href\n- description\n- validFor\n- relatedParty\n- priority\n- isBundle\n- _links" as FULLER_FIELDS
}

PROFILE --> CREATE : submit runtime Intent
CREATE --> RESOLUTION : resolve governing specification
RESOLUTION --> PERSISTED : admission succeeds
RESOLUTION -[#red,dashed]-> CREATE : reject if resolution fails
PERSISTED --> LIFECYCLE : project state and version
PROFILE --> FULLER : may add richer\nimplementation fields

note right of CREATE_RECOMMENDED
humanExpression is not machine-authoritative,
but improves human interpretation,
audit, and triage.

intentSpecification.id is not mandatory,
but improves deterministic validation
and traceability.
end note

note right of RESOLUTION
expression.iri is mandatory.

It is the default runtime
semantic / expression discriminator
when intentSpecification.id is omitted.
end note

note bottom of PERSISTED
Create request may omit
intentSpecification.id.

Persisted/admitted response must
record the resolved specification id.
end note

note bottom of LIFECYCLE
Avoid ambiguous pointer names such as
effectiveVersion or currentVersion.

Use activeVersion where a runtime
version pointer is exposed.
end note

@enduml
